</taxonomicName>
L.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Compositae" genus="Scorzonera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Scorzonera" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Scorzonera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in this revised sense as a monophyletic genus includes four larger clades, the 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Compositae" genus="Scorzonera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Scorzonera" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Scorzonera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.str. clade (3 spp.), 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Compositae" genus="Scorzonera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Scorzonera albicaulis" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albicaulis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Scorzonera albicaulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade (~17 spp.), 
<taxonomicName authority="Lipsch., 1935 (DC.)" authorityName="Lipsch., 1935 (DC.)" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Podospermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Podospermum" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Podospermum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade (~20 spp.) and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Compositae" genus="Scorzonera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Scorzonera purpurea" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="purpurea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Scorzonera purpurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade (2 spp.). In addition, it includes a few, so far somewhat isolated species (
<taxonomicName family="Asteraceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. rupicola" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="rupicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. rupicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName family="Asteraceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. renzii" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="renzii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. renzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName family="Asteraceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. angustifolia" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="angustifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. angustifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The genus in this cricumscription still shows considerable variation. Our analysis is insufficient with respect to a revision of the elaborated infrageneric classifications of previous authors. We therefore refer here to the clades of our trees.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
